-- The supply of water in the Angolan capital Luanda could not be resumed within at least eight days. It is the 10th day today that water supply in Luanda has suspended. Such a suspension of water supply resulted from the cut-off of power supply to the water plant in the suburbs as large rain fell down two high-voltage power supply towers.
